description: Kelly Peters  was  feeling inspired with  Andrew Olson  and  19 others . Last week I was given the most beautiful of gifts. My hometown, childhood home, and the street that made me was totally destroyed. My gift was hope and inspiration. I was able to provide a little support with the help of my fiends and community.   After fear of losing everything I had worked so hard for by an approaching Category 5 Hurricane, it was my friends and loved ones that ended up suffering. My current town was yet again spared from tragedy; however, my hometown was not so lucky.  See, you don't have to be in the direct path of a hurricane to suffer and experience complete and utter devastation. I knew I had to help the ones I loved and the town that built me, so I asked my friends and family for help. I was truly overwhelmed by their response!  Sunday, I packed my large SUV, borrowed a trailer, and I went to help. It was beyond explanation. It hurt so badly to see so many in need, and it felt so good to just be able to do something.   My beautiful gift was to receive an over abundance of help from my friends, and to be able to help others. I also learned that sometimes you just have to act. Support and friendship comes in unexpected ways.   Additionally, I am so proud of the community that built me. Everyone is working together to help one another. It is beyond inspirational!!! Thank you everyone for your help and support.   There are so many in need of help in Florida. Please find some way to help. Manual Labor, organization, and many other skills are just as valuable as items or money to donate.   # Volunteer   # inspired   # blackcreekstrong   # lovethyneighbor   # communityleadership
